inn1.comm: swing straight away for Mills, angles in from slightly wide of the crease and then straightens. Defensively played into the off side
again, nice seam position, searching for away movement, but a little too full. Hafeez punches it back nicely, but Mills fields on his follow through
back of a length outside off, Hafeez stays back and blocks towards point
135 kph, in the channel outside off, invites Hafeez to drive and he times it beautifully but straight to cover
wider outside off, shapes away off the seam and Hafeez lets it go
Mills begins with a maiden, another short of length ball outside off that Hafeez decides to leave

edged, but short of slip. Lovely delivery from Bennett, nips away from back of a length, almost squares up Shehzad as he shapes into a loose drive outside off and it takes the outside edge. It landed just short of a tumbling Taylor at first slip
back of a length outside off and this time it bends back in, Shehzad punches off the back foot towards cover point
takes it wider outside off this time, Shehzad lets it go
a foot and a half outside off at 134 kph, not full enough for the drive and Shehzad sees it through once again

another edge, again from that channel outside off. Shehzad needs to tighten up, this was not full enough for the drive and he is not really driving through the line. This time the edge flies away towards fine leg.

Hafeez shows how it is done. Perfect positioning f the head, easy back lift, meets the ball on the rise and drives a length ball cleanly through the line. It whistles away to the right of mid off, for the first boundary.
Mills dangles this on the pads and Shehzad looks for the tickle round the corner, but finds short fine leg
holds the length back and Shehzad punches with nice timing into the covers
131 kph, darts away off the seam but from well wide of off. Easy leave for Shehzad
Shehzad will be very disappointed here. Another delivery on the pads, he times the glance perfectly but finds short fine leg again.
variety from Mills, an offcutter now, bends back into Shehzad from back of a length, but he lets it go
two maidens on the trot for Mills, finishes with the away seamer outside off and Shehzad is happy to let it go. Quiet start, this
over-pitched outside off, another fluent off drive from Hafeez, but straight to mid off this time
136 kph, holds the length a little back and gets good carry through to B McCullum as Hafeez shoulders arms
just short of a length, searching for an edge, but Hafeez negotiates it well, reaches across, opens the face and steers it to third man
short of good length, Shehzad hangs back and defends into the covers
nice stroke, 136 kph, marginally full and Shehzad drives it on the up into the covers. His placement has not been the best so far

absolutely nothing wrong with the placement on this again. Once again, Bennett over-pitches on the last ball of the over and ruins his good work. Too full, on middle and leg, Shehzad latches on gladly, gets half forward and creams it straight back to the right of the stumps at the non-striker's. It whistles away for four, all along the ground

lovely delivery from Mills, offcutter lands on the seam back of a length, jags back in and bounces extra as Hafeez leaves. The extra bounce makes it hit his belly as he shoulders arms, almost cut him in half
another one on the perfect length outside off, holds its line this time and Hafeez carefully defends to the off side
Mills concedes a run at long last. Straighter delivery, Hafeez is happy to punch it to mid on and get the single
back of a length on off and middle, Shehzad comes forward to a ball he might have been better off playing back to, and drives a little loosely to mid on
half-volley on off, Shehzad moves well into the drive but finds cover
holds it back to end another miserly over, Shehzad tries to force it square off the back foot but finds point
and Bennett bowls contrary to the field. Over-pitched on the pads, Hafeez clips it neatly through square leg for a couple
that's the line, and that's the length. 135 kph on the McGrath corridor outside off, Hafeez hangs back and steers it into the covers
nicely done. Bennett pitches this further up, looking for the edge outside off. Hafeez gets forward, opens the wrists and thumps that through point. Off the middle of the bat, completely in control
Bennett responds with the bouncer, Hafeez seemed to know it was coming. He rocked back and pulled imperiously in front of midwicket. A couple more to the cause.
sharp inducker from Bennett, gets Hafeez into a tangle as he moves forward and across looking to flick. Inside edge, hits him high on the pads.
short cover is in business. Just short of good length, just the length from which it is tough to keep the drive down. Hafeez managed to hit it, a couple of metres short of that fielder
Mills works away on that channel outside off, keeps it on the perfect length too. Shehzad leaves
drifts onto the pads and Shehzad clips it uppishly through midwicket, and that delightful man, Jesse Ryder, fields on the boundary

oh, Hafeez! What have you done! Mills keeps it well short of a length as he has most of the morning. A foot or so outside off. Hafeez could have left it. Or cut it, if he wanted to be adventurous. Or steered it, if he wanted a single. What does he do? He drives. On the up. With his feet miles away from the ball. What happens? It lobs up in the air, straight to mid off.
this one angles in and then holds its line from outside off. And that extra bounce too. Kamran hangs back and leaves
similar ball, ends up wider outside off, Kamran steers from the crease to point
this one stays a touch low, Kamran adjusts and works it to point again. Miserly Mills mesmerises Pakistan. 4-2-2-1
decent pace to start with - 128 kph on a length outside off, no sideways movement and Shehzad leaves

short ball, comes on very slowly off the deck at 125 kph, Shehzad yells "Two" even as he rocks back and pulls it well in front of midwicket. Slightly slow wicket, with sideways movement and extra bounce, this
fuller outside off, Shehzad gets across and defends with the full face down the track
back of a length outside off, Shehzad opens the face and dabs to third man for one
Kamran hangs back in the crease and looks to crunch a square drive, but there is not enough room for him to get it away. Played feebly to point
tidy start from Oram. 128 kph on a length outside off, Kamran presses forward and defends
full on off stump, Shehzad times the off drive very well but finds short cover
134 kph, a foot wide outside off stump and holding its line. Shehzad leaves

lock, stock and two smoking barrells. Shehzad has had enough of letting Mills get away with his tight lines. He improvises by scurrying down the track, while opening up the off side and then whacks this on the rise wide of mid off. Strong swing of the bat and a clean connection
stays in the crease this time and lets one go outside off
closer to the stumps and fuller, Shehzad unfurls another drive, but finds mid off.

the good old heave-ho! Shehzad tramples down the track in a trice and looks for a full delivery. Mills lands this back of a length, but Shehzad does not let him get away with it. Heaves him over midwicket with an agricultural hoick. Not the prettiest shot, but mightly effective
Kamran stays on the crease and defends to the off side
slower ball at 114 kph, stays low outside off and bounces again on the way to Baz as Kamran leaves
closer to the stumps, Kamran stays in the crease and opens the face to steer through the off side

Kamran gets away with an uppish square drive. There is a gully, a short cover and a deeper point in place, but Kamran is very keen on forcing them through the off side. He stays beside this one, not much width on offer, and manages to force it away without full control to the right of diving point. He had to generate all the power on this one, and ended up playing it uppishly as a result
opens the face this time and steers it defensively to Taylor at that short gully kind of position
for the first time today, Kamran plays off the front foot - a loose drive to a delivery that was angling in, and he gets an inside edge to short fine leg
back of a length, angling into Shehzad who is content to stay back and defend him to the leg side

Mills looks for the dream outswinger, the one that lands on leg and moves away. This one, however, despite the perfect seam position, carries on onto the pads. Shehzad doesn't mind that one bit, he happily whips him behind square for four
Shehzad charges out again, short ball in line with the stumps, he opens up the off side and looks to carve over the cordon, but gets an outside edge to third man.
length ball on middle and off, Kamran defends down the track
half volley on off stump, Kamran flows into a drive, but once again, a Pakistan batsman finds a fielder
dot ball to finish the over, short of a length outside off and Kamran looks to steal a single to cover point. The fielder swoops in too quickly though

Shehzad edges through third man for four. Short of a length, tight line just outside off and Shehzad stays back and looks to play the square cut. He is a little late on the shot and it flies away over the slips region and through to the boundary
on the pads this time, Shehzad works it behind square leg
defends a back of length ball outside off into the off side
tight line, offcutter comes in and looks for the lbw, Kamran just about brings the bat down in time to protect the pads and gets a single to mid-on
Shehzad defends cautiously from back of a length outside off

glorious. This is what he was trying to do earlier in the over, but this time he had enough room to work with. Oram lands this well outside off and on a length. Shehzad gets back and across and creams it square with a crack of the bat. Swiped away in style.
over-pitched on off, and yet again Kamran finds a fielder with a crisp drive. Straight to mid off
just back of a length, 135 kph outside off, Kamran goes for the off drive, but hits it to mid off
slow offcutter at 118 kph, Kamran hangs back and angles the face to look for a single, but hits it straight to point

release for Kamran, he's finally placed it to the right of N McCullum at mid off. Length ball on off stump, Kamran gets half across and smashes it hard back past the bowler. McCullum should have stopped that, but dived over it

whoa, take that! Short ball, Kamran seemed to be ready for it. He was back in the crease and ready for the cut. He was so ready for it, he played it early enough for the cut to fly through the covers. Nobody moved as it scurried to the fence
fuller to end the over, Kamran's feet are moving now. Gets forward and check-drives into the covers
short of a length at 124 kph, Shehzad stays back and defends

Pakistan are breaking free here. Shehzad is charging away in style. He was backing away, looking for an off side boundary. Oram saw him move and dropped it short, but gave him the width he wanted. Shehzad opened the face and resisted from over-hitting it as he guided it through point. The timing on that shot was ominous.
fuller length on off, Shehzad promptly pushes forward and takes a single to cover
Kamran looks to steer into the covers for a single, but its not played softly enough
wider outside off, angled face from Kamran as he dabs it straight to point
with the field hanging back for the final ball, Kamran gets the single, pushing a ball on off stump into the covers
short ball, not much width outside off and Kamran goes for the cut. Under-edges it very close to off stump. Hmm ...
back of a length on off stump, Kamran defends to the off side
in line with the stumps this time, Kamran gets behind the line and defends down the track
over-pitched on off and Kamran finds the fielder with another perfectly timed cover drive.
fuller on off, Kamran is early into the shot as he looks to turn it to the on side and gets a leading edge through to mid off for one

boy, Shehzad has hit the leather off this one. The kind of shot you would play in a 'hit it as far as you can' contest. Nothing wrong with the ball - back of a length around off stump. Shehzad gets under it and absolutely smears it over long off. Roundhouse kick that would have done Chuck Norris proud.
turns in from outside off, Kamran steers it well backward of point for a couple
fuller this time, he goes for another steer and finds short third man

Kamran is run out. That's a mad, mad piece of running, to go with a really special piece of fielding. Fuller outside off, Kamran got forward and opened the face, looking to steal a single to the off side. It went quickly to Mills at short third man. Kamran had committed himself to the single and went too far before noticing that Mills had fielded and lined up the stumps even as he was recovering from the tumble. Too late. Dead on throw, on the bounce into the stumps. Gone.
tossed up and turning in, Younis dabs with the spin for one to mid on
hint of spin from McCullum, in line with off stump and defended
turns into the pads from outside off, Shehzad turns it with the spin backward of square leg for one
back of a length outside off, he opens the face and dabs it to point for one
back of a length and coming in with the angle from outside off, Younis is a little early on the punch to the on side and goes with hard hands. Uppish, but safe.
fuller outside off, Younis gets forward and defends to the off side
Shehzad survives a tight run thing. Younis drives straight to Guptill at mid on and takes off for one. Shehzad had to dive in at the striker's end after starting late. A direct hit might have helped
boy, Shehzad is walking all over the crease. Backs away and is on the 10th stump when Styris' 107 kph trundler reaches him. Good line, followed the batsman and cramped him
Younis works with the spin to midwicket. Yes, no, stay situation, but all safe
fuller on off, Younis drives it right back to the bowler
works it off the pads through midwicket this time for a single
Shehzad does it now, gets the pad across and dabs him with the spin to midwicket
Nathan does something he did the other night as well, he slips in the legspinner, at 95 kph with a very quick arm action. Younis doesn't spot it and nearly chips it right back, off the leading edge.
tight line just outside off, Younis rocks back and cuts for one
Styris drifts onto Younis' pads and gets worked away behind square for a single
length ball on off stump, Shehzad gets behind the line and defends
offcutter just outside off and coming in, Shehzad defends down the track
another slow offcutter, on the pads, and clipped straight to midwicket
Shehzad drives a good length ball past mid on and picks a single
over-pitched on the pads, Younis drives it down to long on for another single
enough width outside off for Younis to go back and dab it behind point for one
good bit of running for a chance, Shehzad plays it with hands soft as a baby's bottom towards point and takes off as Baz scurries after it.
turning into the pads, Younis gets across and drives through mid on for one more
full delivery outside off, Shehzad drives against the spin to mid off
too straight, Shehzad gets him away for a single to mid on
Younis goes back in the crease and punches through mid on. Five singles in that over.
Styris lands this too straight and Younis drives to mid on for one
Shehzad now, plays Styris straight to long on for one
on the pads, Younis works it off the pads for a single
slow offcutter on middle and leg, Shehzad drives straight to mid on as Baz yells, "Come on boys, good work, one more ..."
110 kph off cutter on off, defended by Shehzad. "Good work, Scottie," yells BB McCullum.
a fine fifty for Shehzad. Stays beside the line and opens the face from the line of off stump to pick a single into the covers. Well played.
tossed up and turning in, Shehzad drives back to the bowler

cut away for four. Short and wide from Nathan, asking to be carressed backward of point and Shehzad obliged. A comical finish to it all as Jesse Ryder tumbles and rolls over the boundary along with the ball as his sliding save goes wrong
tossed up, closer to the stumps and worked back down the track
full again, this is the line he needs to stick to. Shehzad defends
width this time, Shehzad cuts against this, completely in control against the spin. Surprise, surprise, Jesse gets across from sweeper cover and slides to save a couple this time
turning into the pads, worked with the wrists to midwicket
Younis the single-stealer. Drops a 107 kph off cutter on off stump into the off side and takes off.
short of a length and coming in with the angle, Shehzad guides the pull to square leg, but can't get the gap
this one slides down the leg side, the 100th run for Pakistan.
who had the longer run up there? Shehzad backs away a mile, as Styris begins on his run up. He follows him and keeps it on leg stump, Shehzad has no room and plays into the covers for one

they are scrambling his lines with their footwork. Younis jumps inside the line of leg stump as Styris' legcutter goes wrong. It ends as a full toss on the pads and Younis flicks it easily for four through a vacant fine leg
punches this time with the deviation through long on for one
Shehzad ends the over with another single, driving Styris into the covers for one
turning in from outside off, Shehzad stays beside the line and steers square for one
Younis charges out too far and gets too close to the pitch. He then guides it safely into the covers for one
pre-meditated paddle, was that pad first? Polite appeal for lbw, turned down. It goes straight to short fine leg
drives against the spin towards mid off and gets a single
the more conventional sweep from Younis to a delivery tossed up on off stump, decent connection through square leg
Shehzad chips out, can't reach the pitch and plays defensively down the track to end the over
short ball, angles into Younis who pulls powerfully but straight to Ryder on the ropes
Shehzad backs away a mile and a half, showing Styris all his stumps, but Styris is not interested. Follows him and ensures he can't swing his arms

Shehzad is looking better with every passing delivery. Styris again refused to give him room, so Shehzad created some of his own and generated power out of no where. Back of a length on off stump, he swayed back a touch, waited for it to come beside him and cut it behind square beautifully. Three fielders thought they had a chance to cut it off, but the ball reached the boundary
works this with the deviation to midwicket for a single
Younis promptly returns the strike, dabbing Styris quietly in front of square for one
over-pitched on middle and off, driven back down the ground crisply for one
flighted on off, he opens the face and looks for a late dab. Finds short third man though
Shehzad backs away and looks to carve over the off side, and gets it away to the sweeper cover for one
turning in a touch from back of a length outside off, Younis defends to the leg side

you can travel miles and watch a lot of cricket, but it's unlikely you will see a softer dismissal, or one that is more against the run of play than this one. Nathan lands this on middle and leg and it is harmlessly turning further down. Younis sets himself up for a sweep and he was likely just looking for a single, but he misread the length a touch and got a top edge. It balloons up, straight into square leg's hands, who was standing some distance in. Pakistan have gifted all three wickets today.
short ball, turning down the leg side, worked with the spin to midwicket
quicker ball, 97 kph outside off, Shehzad punches fluently wide of long off for one

Shehzad just can't let Styris get away with his dibbly-dobblers. He back away and looks to flay through the off side. Another offcutter from Styro, follows him outside leg. Shehzad misses, so does Baz and it is four byes.
this time he stays in a more conventional position and clips him with the deviation to midwicket for one
onto the pads, Misbah can't get it away with the turn of the wrists
this time he does, soft little dab behind square leg for one
slides down the leg this time for a wide
length ball on the pads, defended towards mid on
ends the over with a single to long off.
on the pads, Misbah works it with the spin to mid on
this time he gets the single, working Nathan with the spin to midwicket
Shehzad sets himself up early for the lap sweep and gets a single through backward square leg
quicksilver wrists from Misbah, turns him with the spin but can't get the gap
looks to play through the leg side again, but this is too wide outside off and he adjusts the shot at the last moment and steers to short third man
this time he gets the single, working McCullum with the spin off the pads for a single through wide mid on
back of a length and angling across, a bit of an off cutter that. Misbah defends to the off side off the back foot
120 kph, another offcutter that goes away from Misbah who steers to backward point
tighter line, on middle and off, Misbah plays it with a straight bat to mid on
another offcutter at 119 kph, Misbah gets forward and works it through cover point for one
over-pitched on off stump, Shehzad drives to long off for a single
fuller delivery angling across and looking for the edge, Misbah is sucked into the drive, but manages to play it off the meat despite not getting fully across
tossed up outside off, Shehzad chips out of the track and essays a pleasing cover drive along the carpet for a couple.

hmm, a touch of madness in that shot. Shehzad jumps out and tries to Sehwag it over long on. Ends up getting an inside edge as he wasn't near the pitch of the ball and it did not hit anywhere near the middle of the blade. Single to fine leg. McCullum shares his kind opinion with Shehzad.
turning in from middle and off, Misbah defends
gets a single this time, turning it off the pads for one
a foot outside off, enough for Shehzad to cut away behind square for one
Misbah looks for another nurdle round the corner, but can't find the gap

Shehzad has the scoop of the day. He walks across his stumps, finishes on off stump as Franklin looks to angle it across, he's in perfect position for the shot, fine leg is not in the perfect position to save it - he's inside the circle. Shehzad gets it easily over him and on the bounce to the boundary
steers towards How at point and thinks of a single. There's a shy at the stumps that misses and he eventually gets the single
Misbah stays in the crease and guides it quietly to third man for one
Shehzad looks to hit it more violently through square, and gets a thick edge through to third man for one
Misbah, the compulsive flicker. Walks right across the stumps and flicks from outside off to midwicket for one

short of a length and angling across, Shehzad opens up the off side and flays towards deep point for one. He is getting into that zone where he wants to hit everything. Calm down young man, there is a hundred for the taking here.
short ball outside off, cut away against the spin into the covers for one
flighted generously outside off at 77 kph, Misbah gets forward and flick-drives to mid on
short ball, Misbah rocks back and pulls but can't get the gap. Taylor is looking to cut off singles - five men inside the cricle
this time he gets one, cuts him behind point and turns the strike over
Shehzad jumps out, gets too close to the pitch and then drills it along the ground to long on for one
Misbah stays back and defends back to the bowler as it turns in from out side off

"Shehzad... Captain Marvel!" Another scoop. He's scooping the wits out of New Zealand. Walks across outside off again, and makes even better connection that before. Franklin needs to adjust his lines here, or get fine leg back
and now a wide down the leg side as Shehzad daintily steps into line with leg stump
and he wants more! He wants to brutalise Franklin over the leg side. Length ball on off stump, he tries to drop kick it over midwicket. Doesn't middle it at all, but it is safe
stays in the crease and opens the face to steer a single to third man. One of his calmer strokes in recent times.
Misbah looks to cut, too close to the body for the timing to be right.
no-ball, free-hit time now. Over-pitched on off too, Misbah times the off drive perfectly but finds mid off
midwicket is set deep, so Franklin bangs it short and Misbah's pull goes straight to the fielder for a single
back of a length and coming in from outside off. Defended to the off side
ooh, almost a run-out. Misbah works it with the spin straight to midwicket where that man Guptill prowls. He goes down the track and then returns late. A direct hit may have caught him short
and the reverse sweep now. Innovations are the in thing. Not very wide outside off, Misbah pre-meditated it and dabbed it over where slip would have been, for a couple
this one turns in to the pads, works it away square for a single
length ball on the stumps, worked down the ground for one
Misbah goes back and turns him with the spin for a single to midwicket. That's the end of a manic quick spell from McCullum. Phew.
short ball just outside off and Misbah cuts, straight to the only man who could have saved four behind square - backward point.
short again, close to the body for the cut, Misbah stays back and forces into the covers for one

Majestic Shehzad! What awesome batting. Stays back in the crease, gets a back of a length delivery coming into the hitting zone from outside off. Shehzad stays put, swivels his momentum onto the back foot and swings him with disdain over wide long on for a six. You beauty!

surprise, surprise, he's beaten outside off. Just the seconfd time today that I can recall him being beaten, after his first ball that he edged. This one nips away from off stump, good ball from Bennett and even Shehzad can't make connection
99 now. Stays back and quietly taps him into the covers for one

NZ are bleeding runs. Bennett looks for the yorker and sprays it too leg sidish, despite getting it inside the line of Misbah's pads. Misbah does well to move the toes out of the way and squeezes it down to fine leg for four

on 99. 19 years and 72 days old. You would expect a tap and a nervous run. Not with this man. Shehzad chips away merrily to the off side. He gets a back of length ball outside off. He dabs it with the angle to midwicket and becomes the sixth youngest player to ever get an ODI 100. Take a bow!
Misbah gets one angling into the pads and works it through backward square leg for one
tight offcutter coming in from outside off, Shehzad stays put and opens the face to dab a single towards third man
on Misbah's pads again at 125 kph, easily turned away square for one

and a new kind of shuffle now. The front foot stays on leg stump, the back foot goes away exploring the area down the leg side and then comes back into place as Oram bangs short. Shehzad pulls, but not enough room to time the shot well. Single to long on.
attempted yorker, full-pitched on off stump and driven into the off side
length ball on off, and Shehzad seems to have been asked to go after everything. He sees ball and hits ball. Tonks it on the bounce to long off for one
ooh, inducker at 135 kph, Misbah almost gets the inside edge as he looks to cut. Not much room to start with and it kept coming back into him.
length delivery on middle and leg, Misbah looks to heave over the leg side and gets an inside edge towards deep square leg

Shehzad can't be caught inside the playing area. Instead, Umar Akmal, padded up and standing some 20 meters back in Pakistan's player area tries to catch it. And even he can't! Shehzad sways back onto the back foot, gets a juicy length ball coming in for the drive and he pummels it over long on. That went right up into the clouds before coming down. Shehzad just stands and admires his own shot. He might have been worried for his team mates.
and he takes a single now, this is not just brutal, but brainy as well.
Misbah looks to force a single through point but can't get it away
back of a length on middle and off, Shehzad backs away but there's no room to go hard at it. Single to point
full ball on middle, Misbah drives down the ground for a single to long on

Shehzad is not so much toying with the bowling as discarding them like old rag dolls. He's moved away to the leg side again, Styris looks to follow him but can't completely cramp him this time. Shehzad inside outs him with clinial precision over the covers and wide long off can't get across to cut it off.

end of a memorable innings. Shehzad has perished in his attempt to hit another six. Fuller length from Styris, Shehzad was lining up the stands at deep midwicket, but he got too far under it. Ended up scooping it high and when it came down, James Franklin was there to take the steepler. Pakistan in complete charge, all the same. What an innings.
Misbah hangs in the crease and plays softly into the covers for another single
slow offcutter to end the over, he comes forward and defends to the off side
back of a length outside off, Misbah taps it through point for a single
angles this one into Umar as he looks to work it off the pads square. Can't get it away though
Umar is away, steering fluently behind point as Oram over-pitches. I just realised Umar and Oram are almost anagrams.
length ball at 127 kph, Umar gets forward and defends to the off side.
drifts onto the pads this time and Umar works it behind square for one.
Misbah backs away and looks to thump over the covers, but it is too full and he can't quite get under it
back of a length, Umar stays back and steers behind point for one
Misbah looks to heave over midwicket, but again the timing is not perfect. Dribbles away to deep midwicket for one
Umar flicks off the pads to fine leg for one.

Misbah is gone. Never quite looked the part today - rare off-day for him on tour. Looks for the loft over the leg side again, going well deep in the crease as it is angled into his body. He was in position for the shot, but did not make a clean connection. It is lofted harmlessly towards deep square leg for a smart tumbling catch by Oram. He seemed to have over-run the ball as he moved to his right, but adjusted well with the hands to pouch it just above the turf
full on middle and leg, driven to long on for one
Umar opens the face and dabs in front of point for a single
129 kph, very full on middle and leg, not much Umar can do with it. He digs it out to mid on
back of a length outside off, Umar looks to pinch a single to the off side, but misses the gap
another full ball, cramping him for room on leg stump, Umar drives to long on for one
Afridi gets across and opens the face to guide a single without violence in front of point
on the pads, Afridi looks to flick it away, but is early on the shot and misses
Afridi is revving it up, looks to hit one hard through the covers, but finds the fielder. A polite suggestion that he won't be operating at a Strike rate of 25 for too much longer.
on the pads, Umar works it off the pads through square leg for one
oh boy, Afridi sets up a stiff breeze around the ground with an almighty swoosh at a length ball angling into his pads at a friendly pace. He was beaten by the lack of pace.

not this time. At Styris' pace, he can't over pitch, or land it on leg stump. He did both this time. Afridi must have felt insulted at being offered such an easy scoring opportunity. He just swipes it from his presence over deep midwicket. Another six for the man with most sixes.
ooh, looks to brutalise a length ball over midwicket again, but this time he doesn't get the elevation. It thunders away to the man on the deep for a single
Umar does the smart thing - stays beside the line and runs it square for a single

Afridi is lining 'em up here. Backs away, exposes the stumps and Styris follows him. He smears the short of length ball with furious power through midwicket, but there are several men patrolling that boundary.
slower offcutter at 112 kph, Afridi waits and turns it with the movement through square leg

delicate from Umar, barely a few inches wide of off stump, he walks into it and opens the face to run it really fine. Styris at third man does well to get there, but did he stop it cleanly? He puts in the slide, and lets go of it just before releasing the ball. It is clean, well done.
banged in short at 129 kph, Umar can't do much with it, stays back and drops it to the leg side
slower ball again outside off, Umar spots it early and check drives into the covers for one
hmm, low full toss on off stump, Afridi can't get under it and just bunts to long on for a single
another slow offcutter, this time Umar can't get the gap. He steers it straight to short third man
and he's too straight to begin with. Wide down the leg side
full toss, but crucially the line is good. Afridi forehands to the deep for one
on Umar's pads, he turns the wrists late and gets a single square
nice slower ball at 114 kph, Afridi spots it very late. He was looking for the booming loft down the ground  before reining himself in and working it to midwicket for one
full toss on off stump and he bunts down to long on for one

whoa, Afridi plays the lofted straight drive, but in the opposite direction - over McCullum's head. Back of a length on off, Afridi plays his version of the scoop and looks all at sea. Nearly plays it back onto his own body. Why would you do that when you can bang them down the ground in the conventional manner?
low full toss on leg stump, Afridi muscles it to long on for another single. Quiet start to the PP

Afridi picks four with a very clever shot to a not very clever ball. The field is in on the off side as Afridi backs away, and Mills delivers a full delivery well outside off. Afridi was almost too far away, but managed to reach it with a huge stretch and guide it square for four

low full toss on middle and leg, Afridi tries to launch it past mid off, but can't get it past. Tight single, he has to run around Mills and dive to get in, but the throw misses. All smiles after Afridi's tumble
Umar moves away now and looks to inside out Mills over the infield on the off side. Can't time it well and gets a single as it is fielded at cover.
low full toss on off, that's a good option at this stage and even Afridi can't get under it. Drags it away to long on for one

nice work from Umar, confuses Mills with his movement around the crease. He first moves the back foot across to off stump, then the front foot, then pulls the back foot back to leg stump and opens up the off side for the carve. Mills' line, no doubt scrambled by the movement, is on off stump and it is a nice hittable full toss that is thumped flat through the covers.
Umar is nearly run out at the bowler's end as he looks to steal a single to point. Franklin (I think) throws the stumps down at the bowler's end as he hustles in, just in time.
slower ball, at 114 kph well outside off, Umar decides to deal with it without violence. Single to point
full toss on the pads, Afridi gets inside the line and flick-swats behind square leg. He runs hard for the second. McCullum, by the way, is keeping without the pads. Haven't seen that too often.
another single, this time off Afridi's pad as he's early into a similar shot to a slower ball.
full length ball on middle and leg, Umar drives to long on for a single

Afridi gone, this is a big wicket in the context of the game with 4.1 overs to go. Short ball, around off stump, and Afridi looks to fore-hand cross-court it down the ground. He ends up top-edging it the shot and it is an easy catch for long on running in. Over to Razzaq and Umar now.
good delivery, follows him as Umar backs away and cramps him completely for room. Umar looks to pull, but it is not short enough and he misses.
yorker on leg stump at 133 kph and Razzaq digs it out to long on for one
good lines from Mills, very straight, yet not straying down the leg side and Umar can't du much except force it down the ground for one
Razzaq makes room to the leg side, Mills follows him and ensures Razzaq can't flex those biceps. Still manages to get it away through wide long on for a couple

New Zealand are making the batting Powerplay work against Pakistan here. Razzaq falls now. Length ball, it was there for the loft over long off and Razzaq made decent connection, but could not clear the boundary rider.

amidst all the madness, Umar Akmal produces a class shot. Slower ball in line with off stump at 110 kph. No room to hit it hard, no pace to work with. So Umar instead chooses to make use of the principle of placement and pick a boundary. He just waits for the right moment, opens the face and cuts it in purpose in front of square and in between all the men inside the circle on the off side
steers the final delivery straight to short third man for a single
Jake produces a perfect yorker, 128 kph on middle and leg, Umar digs deep in the crease, goes down and steers with an angled bat to short third man.
clever little slower bouncer, 112 kph, Riaz is completely befuddled by the slowness of it as it balloons past him. He just ducks.
slower off cutter, and Riaz is years early into the shot. B McCullum muffs it as it comes through on the second bounce. Was he concerned since he did not have the pads on? A couple more.
another off cutter, this time more pacy, at 124 kph. Riaz looks to pull, mostly in hope, and misses again. McCullum doesn't

Riaz connects at long last. He's barely spotting this slow off cutters, and is again too early into the pull. The ball comes after his swing, hits the toe-edge and goes through mid on for one. Bizarre.
well bowled, Jacob Oram. Full delivery on Umar's pads to end the over, and despiute moving across his crease furiously, Umar can't get under it. He drives a single to long on
another very slow slower ball, 112 kph and Umar waits a while before swat-pulling ti wide long on. NZ have set their fields cleverly. Their best fielders are on the deep on the leg side
another slow off cutter, 114 kph, another swish and a miss from Riaz. Umar is almost expecting him to miss, he takes an early start and they steal a bye.

another one, 115 kph, short of a length and angling in. New Zealand have done really well in these last few overs. Umar is unable to pack a punch again and his frustrated pull dribbles out to deep midwicket for one

Umar is run out. Well donw Brendon McCullum. No one seems to expect Riaz to connect. Umar backs up a mile once again. McCullum knows they are likely to steal another bye, so he takes a start as well. True to form, Riaz swings wildly at a full ball outside off and misses. McCullum collects and under-arms a throw at the striker's end in a trice. Umar, despite the early start, is caught short.
slow offcutter to Gul, 108 kph to begin with and Gul's not been seeing the action recently. He did not seem to anticipate the slower ball at all, and it gripped and came back into his pads
slow, slower, slowest. Afridi will bowl faster than that later tonight. Offcutter at 104 kph, short and completely befuddles Umar who swipes in hope and misses.
low full toss on the pads, Gul gets inside the line and whips it square for a single
another slow offspinner, back of a length at 114 kph and despite his best attempts, Riaz can't time the pull shot. Skies it towards deep midwicket for one
faster this time, a foot outside off and Gul clearly fooled by the pace again. Attempts a pull and misses on the second try
and now a faster ball, short again and Gul is hurried into a pull. All the same, he makes no contact. Almost a run out as he looks to run a single off the body, but they pull out of it.
another dot ball, Pakistan have stalled on second gear. Gul backs away, Oram follows him, Gul swings, it goes through between stumps and the batsman. You know the drill.

surprise, surprise! Gul has connected. But sadly for Pakistan, he's holed out. Short of a length, outside off, Gul manages to get a good piece of it as he stays back and carves over the off side. He finds the man sweeping square on the off side. Pakistan's last five overs have yielded 25/4.

inn2.comm: and Ryder is run out without facing a ball! Back of a length in line with middle and off, Guptill stays on the crease and pushes it to mid-on. Ryder comes out of the crease thinking of a single, and turns back too late. The throw from Misbah running across from midwicket was dead accurate and Ryder's short by more than a foot. Guptill made a start, but backed out. Ryder - out injured for two games, in a twitter rant, and now this. What horrendous luck! Misbah had one stump to hit and he did.
and a leave that hits the bat. Back of a length outside off, Guptill thinks of playing before pulling the bat away late. The ball hits the bat and goes into the slips.. One the bounce.
and he's away. Cracks away a short ball outside off crisply past point and through for four. Nicely controlled
very straight, Guptill looks to play it to the on side but can't get it away
too straight from Razzaq, and it takes the pads on the way to the fine leg boundary. Bristling start to the chase!
back of a length outside off, Guptill leaves and thats the end of a manic first over
back of a length, fast and furious outside off and How chooses to leave
on the stumps this time, How gets behind the line and defends down the track
he's cranking it up now. 146 kph, hits the deck and pushes How back in the crease. He manages to ride the bounce and steer it square for one
147 kph, back of a length again outside off and glorious timing from Guptill as he stands tall and punches it into the covers
lets this one go through as it whistles past, outside off stump at 147 kph.
searching for the pads at 149 kph - Boy, this man never drops pace! Guptill brings the bat down just in time to squeeze it towards square leg
that kept low, 125 kph and on a length. How was playing back to it, and just managed to come down and get an inside edge on it
comes forward into an off drive and times it well, but straight to mid off
gets forward again to a length ball at 129 kph around off stump, and defends carefully towards extra cover
straighter this time, ends on middle and leg, How plays the on-drive but finds mid on
marginally short of a length and How is eager to get going, so goes for a pull shot though it wasn't short enough for the shot. It is through him quickly though.
over-pitched but How misses out, driving crisply but straight to mid off
pacy again from Shoaib, comes in with the angle and finishes on middle and leg, Guptill check drives to mid on
short ball outside off at 149 kph and Guptill tries to force the cut away. Can't quite middle it and hits it straight into the turf. They run a quick single to point
148 kph now, Shoaib looks like he's run a marathon already, wheezing and whistling through his delivery stride. Back of a length and on the money, defended back down the track
slower ball of sorts - 129 kph (There are some bowlers whose fastest is 129 kph), How adjusts to the lack in pace and guides it to backward point for a single

inventive batting, and brave batting. 149 kph and short of a length, he stays on the crease, gets half forward and just swings straight back through the line. Doesn't middle it, but gets enough muscle behind it for four straight down the ground. Shoaib lets out a confused smile.
searing bouncer, aimed at the head, 143 kph, and Guptill wisely gets inside the line and lets it go
150 kph, ladies and gentlemen. Short of a length and steep bounce to hurry Guptill back in the crease. He still looks to find a way to force it square and gets a thick inside edge to square leg
sprays down the leg, How walks inside the line and looks to lap-swat it round the corner, it hits the pad on the way to Kamran who appeals for caught behind. Turned down.
nice stuff from Razzaq, 131 kph, back of a length on off stump, the batsman has to take a risk if he wants four. How chooses to stay in the crease and defend down the track
the legcutter now, almost induces a leading edge from How who looks to work it off the pads to the leg side. It moves away and is edged back towards the bowler
he gets a single eventually, getting across and opening the face to steer backward of point
on Guptill's pads, worked square for a single
tidy end to the over, How punches a length ball crisply down to long on for a single
tight lines from Shoaib, keeps it on off, How can't do much with it. Defended into the covers

that's the weirdest sort of top edge you will see. 140 kph short ball, How goes for the pull and is incredibly, early on the shot. He ends up getting it on the glove and splice and it balloons up between him and the keeper.
another pacy short delivery, and again he's early on the pull and gets it straight to mid on. How's getting a little stuck here
some release, How opens the face and dabs a couple through backward poiny. It came at 146 kph and he just had to deflect it, almost all the way
better line, closer to off stump, How tries to play to the off side, but has no room to force it
finishes with another quick delivery on off stump. Not there for the drive, the cut or the pull. How defends down the track
full length ball, comes into the pads and is punched towards long on for one
awry shot selection again from How, pulling a ball that's not neat short enough. Gets it down to long on, for a single
a rare delivery that's off line, and Guptill puts it away. Length ball, angling in towards leg stump, Guptill gets his momentum from inside the line and swings it through midwicket.
full again, but outside off and Guptill drives into the covers for a single
holds the length back and this time How just punches back down the ground with the full face for one. Better option than those mis-hit pulls.

innovation from Guptill. It was there for the drive as Razzaq landed it full outside off, but Guptill was mindful of the crowd inside the circle in the covers. He waited that extra moment, opened up his wrists and placed it between cover and point for four
short of a length outside off, incredible discipline considering how fast he's bowling. Played away defensively to the off side off the back foot
this one angles in from around off stump as How looks to play the flick. He's again early on the shot and gets a leading edge to the left of the pitch
pushes him back with a short ball at 143 kph, How does well to ride the bounce and drop it to point where Misbah prowls away. He has a shy at the bowler's end, but misses.

whoa, and he produces a ripper, despite the bad knee. 147 kph, a touch of away shape off the deck. Guptill plays inside the line from the crease and looks befuddled as it whizzes past the outside edge
shorter, no room at all for Guptill to work with and he makes a big effort to force the cut shot. He gets it away, but can't beat point
short ball, 144 kph to end the over, Guptill seemed ready for it and pull straight to deep square leg for a single
decent delivery to begin with, angling across off a tight line at 136 kph and Guptill check-drives to mid off
on the pads this time, Guptill stays in the crease and clips it square for a single
over-pitched at 139 kph and How flows into a nice-looking drive, but straight to Afridi at wide mid-off
the pace is improving, 141 kph now and How presses forward to a length ball and defends to the off side
NOTHING is working for How. He's completely stuck. He now tries to walk across his stumps and find a half volley somewhere, and he gets one on off stump, which he lamely drives back to the bowler.
back of a length and angling across, How looks to dab it towards fine leg for one, but still can't find the gap
he begins with one on the pads and Guptill works it square for a single. How has strike again.
141 kph, back of a length outside off - Pakistan have been extremely disciplined with the ball so far. How can't do much with bad balls, leave alone good ones. Defended with an angled face to point
slightly fuller on off, How looks for the square drive and gets a thick edge towards third man

that's a rare poor ball. Gul sprays it on the pads as he searches for a pacy yorker. It is 147 kph, but when over-pitched on the pads, the speed is detrimental to the bowler's cause. Guptill sparkles with a whip off the toes and it speeds away to midwicket
better line, gets it outside off and holds the length back as well. Guptill defends to the off side
and further outside off to end the over, Guptill leaves as it nips away off a length.
on the pads, they get a leg bye as Jamie (I'll refer to him thus from now) misses the flick.
short of a length on the hips, and Guptill does well to nudge it softly through backward square leg. They hustle across quickly for a couple
144 kph, back of a length and angling across from middle to leg. Guptill stays on the back foot and defends with a full face
whangs this down the leg side at 145 kph. Guptill misses the swing through square leg and gets a wide
and now he angles one across Guptill, who is beaten outside off as he gets neither forward nor back and has a feel at it.
on the pads this time, Guptill misses out on a boundary opportunity. Well-timed flick but straight to midwicket, so just a single
another failed attempt by Jamie to steer a single square. He plays it straight to point
back of a length and angling into the batsman, who stays back and looks to work it to the leg side.
fuller and angling across, Guptill looks to check drive and finds the fielder at cover
Guptill advances, he is getting fidgetty. Comes down the track and looks to open up the off side, but Gul keeps it straight and short of a length. Guptill goes for the carve over the cover and misses
another dot. Fuller length on off stump, he opens the face and guides it straight to point
angles into the body and Guptill nudges square for a single. The return from Umar Akmal in the deep hits the stumps inadvertently and concedes a second
and ends with another dot ball, tight line just outside off, Guptill goes for a half-hearted cut and misses. He didn't have the room to make it happen
How gets to the other end early. Stays back and plays with really soft hands towards point, and takes off for NZ's 50th run
short ball, ends on middle and leg, Guptill clips off the pads through midwicket for one
ooh, that nipped back in a touch as Jamie went for an on-drive without getting to the pitch. He got the inside edge through to midwicket
back of a length and sliding across Guptill who stays back and dabs it very fine for one
as tight as tight lines get. Back of a length, landing on middle, finishing on off, Jamie can only defend off the back foot

Jamie's agonising stay at the crease gets out with a shot that typified the innings. It was just back of a length, not the right delivery for the pull, but Jamie's built so much pressure on himself, he resorted to his favourite shot to effect the jailbreak. He stayed on the crease and looked to pull/swing it in the air over midwicket. Alas, it got big on him as he went for the shot and the top edge popped up towards deep midwicket. All over for How.
back of a length outside off, he comes half forward and defends with an angled face into the covers
hint of inward seam movement there, as it lands back of a length outside off at 141 kph and suggests that it's coming in. Taylor leaves
and now he gets one to jump up off the track, from back of a length. 140 kph and Taylor was looking to come forward. He had to take the top hand off in a hurry as he defended.
Taylor is away with a cheeky single. Short of a length outside off and he opens the face to guide just past a fumbling point for a single
this one drifts into Guptill's body and he works it square for a single
short of a length outside off to end the over, Taylor lets it go as it holds it line
has there been anything to drive today from Pakistan? Another one on the perfect length outside off, Guptill stays beside the line and defends
he looks to wait and steer one behind square, but can't beat the man at point
finally something closer to Guptill's half and he pounces on it with glee. Driven back crisply, but Riaz gets a hand on it to slow it down
fuller length, a foot wider outside off stump and Taylor leaves
another leave outside off from Taylor, he walks across and shoulders arms to a back of length ball that angles across
on the hips and Taylor works it round the corner for a single. They think of two, but Hafeez charges in from the deep to deny the second
Gul gets one to straighten marginally from off stump line, Taylor gets forward and adjusts to cover for the deviation
on Taylor's hips this time, he works it nicely off the hips but finds midwicket
legcutter at 139 kph outside off, Taylor manages to use the room and cut it square for one.

I've seen appeals, and I've seen Gul's implore to the umpire just now. Boy, that was incredible. Guptill, meanwhile, has survived a very close lbw call. Nipping in prodigiously from a length just outside off as Guptill gets into a tangled attempt to play to the off side. He misses and it strikes the front pad adjacent to off. It was hitting middle. Gul turned back and put his hands out in appeal. He then began appealing in a polite manner to begin with. No response from the umpire. He threw his arms wider, opened his mouth wider and shouted louder. The umpire shook his head. The third appeal was in pure despair. He just yelled in pure frustration, bending forward with arms by his side, every bit of his body language communicating incredulity. Ian Smith on air says that was "Stone Cold out". I agree. Umar Gloom.
Taylor defends from outside off towards point.
picks a single off the last ball, plays carefully into the covers for a single
back of a length and angling across, Taylor looks to work it to the leg side, but gets a leading edge down the track
just enough room outside off for Taylor to go for the cut, and he managed to time the shot pretty well. There was cover at third man though.

terrific work from Gul at fine leg. Full length and angling across Guptill, who set up a strong base and slashed hard at it. It carried almost all the way to Gul, but landed on the half volley and spun viciously away, but he put a hand out and stopped it inside
one of those rare poor deliveries from Pakistan and Taylor was almost taken by surprise. Riaz lands a friendly half tracker outside off and Taylor obliges with a slap through the covers
on the pads and worked through square leg for a single
short ball on the body and it is dabbed towards short fine leg for one
short of a length from Gul, Guptill stays on the crease and nudges it off the body to the leg side
fuller length this time, in line with the stumps and he gets some pad on it for a leg bye
short of a length outside off, Taylor stays back and pushes it into the off side
again in that neither here nor there length, Taylor stays back and steers into the covers for a single

and how close was that to the stumps? Soft hands can be a good thing, unless they get too soft for comfort. Guptill stays back and drops a back of length ball so gingerly that it nearly rolls back onto the stumps.
not there for the drive again, Guptill stays put and cuts away square for another single
skidder that hurtles across from off to leg, he stays back and forces it through mid on
gets the single this time, 100 kph and forcing Guptill back again, but he plays it straight to long on
lively nurdle from Taylor. Afridi drifts on the pads, Taylor gets inside the line and tickles it into the vast vacancy square on the leg side. He's back for two too.
in line with middle and off this time, Taylor looks to work it through the off side, but finds point
shot from Taylor. Afridi over-pitches outside off, Taylor got across to the pitch and smoothly drove it into the gap in the covers. Fluent and elegant.
quicker one, searching for the lbw, but Taylor was ready this time, brought his bat down on it and defended to the leg side
136 kph, loosener by his standards to start off, and it seemed to surprise Guptill who was early on the check drive from the crease. Down to a slow-moving Gul at long
back of a length again, this time around off stump and played with an angled face towards point
Taylor gets inside the line and clips a delivery slanting into his pads towards square leg for a single
slower ball, 123 kph and still well back of driving length outside off. Guptill waits and waits before forcing into the covers for a single
Taylor drops it softly to mid on where Gul is clearly struggling and picks a single despite playing off the back foot
ooh, 143 kph bouncer, and Guptill nearly chops it back onto the stumps. He was beaten by the pace there and was late on the shot. Went quite close to the stumps, but missed
in line with off stump, played with the minimal turn into the covers
quicker one, hurries into Guptill in line with middle and leg. No room to improvise and he just keeps it out

another quicker one from Afridi, 98 kph, but you can't give room at that pace. Guptill is ready, waits for it to cross him and them dabs it smartly between Shehzad at point and a tired Shoaib who gives up early at short third man

fifty for Guptill, and very well played. The more conventional cut this time as Afridi drops slightly short and wide enough at 89 kph and Guptill made all the pace himself. Cut it squarer than the previous shot and beat the man running across from sweeper cover
fuller from Afridi, Guptill goes for the pull and miscues. Single to midwicket
four more, huge over for New Zealand this. Afridi gives Taylor just enough room to entice the cut shot, but Taylor outside edges it due to the extra pace and it flies away through the vacant slips.
back of a length and in line with the stumps, Guptill gets behind the line and defends

NZ are effecting the jailbreak here. Majestic from Martin. Glorious from Guptill. Short of a length again, but there was enough width this time. Guptill stays back and swishes at it like he's weilding a magic wand. Abracadabra. Four through point.
effort ball, 142 kph and angling into the body. Huge grunt from Shoaib at release, Guptill tucks it square for a single
better line this time, Taylor just gets behind it and defends
and now a bouncer, Taylor wants nothing to do with it and ducks away
another short one, 141 kph and this time Taylor has a go at the hook shot. It is through him in no time though.
turns in from a length around off stump and is worked with the spin to midwicket
not sure how that missed. It kept low from middle and off line, Guptill was really late in bringing the bat down, but got the inside edge to fine leg for one
Taylor drives with the spin to mid on
turning down the leg, Taylor gets inside the line and clips with the spin behind square.
Guptill leans out to open the face and steer against the spin for one through point

another huge lbw shout, this time Umpire Tony Hill rules in NZ's favour. Lots of gamesmanship as the ball was being bowled. Trigger movement from Taylor suggested he was going to charge across to off stump, Hafeez saw him and stopped atr delivery stride and then delivered flat and full on off. It turned in as Taylor went for the slog sweep .. and missed. Huge appeal as it struck the pads. Hill had a good look and said no. Replays say it would have just clipped leg stump. Marginal call.

rub of the green not going Pakistan's way here. Leg cutter from Shoaib at 141 kph, Guptill knew nothing of it as he felt for it and got a thick outside edge straight to where first slip would have been.
gets a single this time, staying back and steering square
Taylor stays back and check drives into the covers for another single
Guptill gets another short ball outside off and cuts it behind square for another single
now Taylor gets a single towards third man as he opens his wrists and walks into a square drive.

and a wicket out of nowhere. Guptill's thrown it away. Short ball, it was there for the pull, but considering Shoaib's extra pace, he may have wanted to keep it down. Instead, Guptill went aerial. And holed out to the man at deep midwicket. It was a very good bouncer mind you, effort in that ball, just outside off, and caught Guptill by surprise and he was actually not looking at the ball when he played it.
Hafeez turns one into Taylor who works it square but can't get the single
again, works it with the spin into the leg side.

mad running, but Taylor survives. Turns down the leg, he gets it away to backward square leg and starts late as Baz charges down the track. A direct hit from Younis would have had him, but the throw wasn't accurate
flighted on middle and leg, McCullum flicks with the spin to mid on
again turning into the pads, McCullum defends with the full face down the track

dropped! McCullum's been put down by Hafeez on 0. This could be crucial. Hafeed did almost everything right there .. He tossed it up, he invited McCullum out of the crease, he deceived him in the flight, he got him to chip it back. And then he botched it. Straight in, straight out.
Taylor gets one outside off on a length and defends to the off side
pacy ball on middle and leg, McCullum just gets behind the line and defends down the track
effort again, 145 kph and pumped up on middle and leg, McCullumstaunch in defence
McCullum shows how to play the pull. Pacy bouncer on off, he gets over the bounce and rolls his wrists to keep it down. Hit like a bullet to deep square leg for one
Taylor looks to drive into the covers for a single, but can't find the gap
and now an offcutter, 146 kph and coming into the pads, Taylor nudges off the pads but finds midwicket. Fine spell from Shoaib. This is likely the end of it.
angled face from Baz, opens the wrists and steers for a single behind point
Taylor gets across for another lap shot and makes connection this time. Single to square leg
McCullum jumps out of the crease, but it is short of a length and he just bunts it to long on for one
another pre-meditated lap shot from Taylor, gets it down to fine leg this time for one
McCullum stays back and goes hard at a ball that turns in and stops on him. Safely down to long on though.
Taylor shuffles across and works Hafeez with the spin through square leg for another single
speared into the pads and driven down to wide mid on for one
McCullum stays beside the line and drives inside out into the covers for one
Taylor opens the bat face and angles it straight to short third man. They wisely decide against a single
full on the stumps and Taylor drives through mid on for another single
McCullum gets a single this time, driving through mid on as Afridi bowls too straight
Taylor looks for tha late cut, but can't beat point.
Brendon plays the reverse sweep, but can't get it fine enough to beat short third man
now Brendon bustles down the track, and Hafeez holds the length back. He ends up whacking it without grace through mid on for one
Taylor comes across and works him with the spin through square leg for another single
slips this wide down the leg, perhaps expecting another charge from Brendon. He stays in the crease though.
this time Brendon dances out and Hafeez holds it back again, Brendon defends back towards mid on
fuller outside off, McCullum reaches out and defends with bat and pad
back of a length and turning down the leg side, quietly worked with the spin to Misbah at midwicket
speared in on leg stump, bunted down to long on for one
good running from Baz, a bit of room outside off and he drives it into the covers and charges across for a couple

McCullum is gone in a mad swoosh into the Hamilton night. Afridi flights this one on middle and leg and gets it to turn ever so slightly. McCullum moved the front foot across and looked to hack high and across the line. He ended up getting a top edge that just went straight up and was taken safely at long on
on Taylor's pads, driven past mid on for another single
drift in towards leg stump and then turn, Styris spots it and drives fluently with the spin past extra cover
89 kph on middle stump, it seemed to stop on Taylor as he got forward and looked to work it across the line.
Styris stays in the crease and runs Hafeez off the face but straight to short third man
turns in from off, Styris hangs back and plays through mid on for one
Taylor reaches out to the pitch of the ball and works him with the spin through mid on
back of a length and defended back down the track
Styris drives against the spin and gets a single through mid off

smart work from Hafeez, but ends up conceding a run. Tossed up and driven back, Styris had meandered out of the crease. Hafeez tried to deflect it on to the stumps as Styris hurried back in, but it missed.
short ball, but too close to off for the cut. Taylor forces straight to point
fired in at 101 kph, Taylor nearly scoops it into midwicket's hands but gets a single to wide long on
short and a little wide outside off, Styris cuts through point for one
width again for Taylor, who plays into the covers and takes another single
Styris stays in the crease and drives with the spin for another single into the covers
inward drift to end the over, Taylor keeps it out
turns in from outside off, Styris opens the face to dab against the spin through point for one
holds it back and gets it to stop and turn into Taylor who defends down the track
this time Taylor gets the single, turning the wrists through square leg for one
flighted on off, Styris drives it back to the bowler
drifting onto the pads, Styris clips it through midwicket for one
boy, are the spinners hustling through the overs or what! Taylor looks to steer through point, but can't get it away
flighted on the pads, he's worked it against the spin through midwicket for one
Styris lunges out to reach the pitch to a back of length ball outside off and defends
turns away from off again, and Styris defends into the off side once more
finally gets the single, through the leg side

huge lbw appeal, turned down. Clever stuff from Afridi, quick and straight, homing onto the pads as Taylor looks to work it across the line, eyeing the gaps on the leg side. May have hit just outside the line of off.
he gets the single this time, pushing him with the spin through the covers
Taylor leans out to the line outside off, gets to the pitch and works him with the spin to midwicket
the floater, gets the leading edge as Taylor looks to turn it to the on side from well outside off. Single to point
Styris dabs to short third man and gets a tight single as Taylor hares across in a flash.
tossed up outside off, Taylor reaches out and opens the face to take a single through point
turning into the pads, Taylor waits and works it with the spin through midwicket. 150 up.

Styris is run out. Superb throw from short Younis at short fine leg. Taylor tickled it round the corner and set off for a quick run. Styris came across immediately, but it was always going to be tight. Younis just detonated the stumps with a laser throw. Styris tumbled in, diving full length, but to no avail.
flighted outside off, driven with the spin into the covers
Taylor works this off the pads through backward square leg for one
Franklin plays a shot from another era. Googly from Afridi, angling across Franklin who spots it, leans across languidly and caresses it almost carefully through the covers. Shot.
another wrong 'un, stops and jumps across Franklin, who carefully defends off the back foot
this time he gets the single, driving down to long off
on Taylor's pads and he drives towards long on for another single
turning into Taylor's pads, he gently nudges it to midwicket
92 kph, through quickly to Taylor who drives it back to the bowler
stays back and looks to force him through mid on. Still can't get the single
four dots to the part-timer. Taylor flicks one sprayed down the leg side, straight to short fine leg
back of a length and turning into Taylor who punches it through to long on for a single
bite and turn away from Franklin who nearly taps it back to Hafeez.
drfiting into the pads, Taylor gets the pad across and works him through square leg
turning in from middle and leg, Franklin flicks straight to midwicket
Franklin stays well back in the crease and guides to deep cover for one.
on the pads, Taylor drives to long on for his 50th run. It's been a bit of a struggle though.
full on middle and leg, Franklin digs it out to mid on for a single
90 kph, on a length around middle and off, Taylor looks to work him across the line but can't get it away. Again.
Franklin gets a single first ball, they need more off Hafeez. A lot more.

at long last, Taylor opens up against Hafeez. Length ball on middle and off, turning in, he got the front foot across and played his pet shot - the slog slam over midwicket. One of the people in the crowd in the grassbanks nearly impales himself on the fence trying to catch that one. Thats a lot of risk for the cash award.
fuller from Hafeez, he drives down the ground for one.
Franklin gets a single now, finally something that looks like a decent over.
Taylor drives with the spin through mid on for one
fired in on the pads at 102 kph, Taylor clips it through midwicket for a single
turning away from Franklin who stays back and steers it square for a single
tossed up and drifting into middle and leg line, driven with the spin through mid off for a single
on Franklin's pads and he looks to turn it round the corner. Straight to short fine leg
drives the fifth ball down to long on for a single. They need boundaries.
flipper of sorts from Afridi nearly gets through Taylor's attempt to cut. It missed the bat and thudded into the pads, but outside the line of off
back of a length and angling into Franklin who looks to work it into the on side. Not well timed, but enough for a single
and he's over-stepped. In the Powerplay. Can Taylor make it count? Strays on the pads and Taylor obliges by turning it away through square leg for two. The field can't change.

nicely done Taylor. It was a tough ball to get away, just fuller than the perfect driving length, on off stump and angling across. Taylor got under it and dliced a drive over mid off inside the circle. Seven runs off one ball.
a slight hint of reverse swing, at 146 kph, it homes into Taylor's pads. He manages to flick it away square for one more
back of a length on off stump, Franklin stays on the crease and drives towards mid off for another single
slow legcutter at 106 kph, Taylor picked it and steers it through the covers for a single
ooh, tight. That wasn't too far from being legitimate. Called wide on the off side.
slow offspinner of sorts on the pads, Franklin spots it and nurdles square for one. Good start to the PP for NZ
on middle and leg, Franklin dabs with the spin through mid on for one

another tight lbw call turned down. Skidder at 106 kph, landed back of a length, beat Taylor's attempt to turn it to the leg side and thudded into the knee roll in front of leg stump. That was hitting leg. Luncky.
Afridi is angry! From two paces, he delivers at 128 kph! Taylor just about keeps it out. Single to mid off
Franklin gets a single now and turns it back to the captain.

Captain gets captain. Finally an lbw goes Pakistan's way. Afridi slowed this one up through the air, landed it on middle and off. Taylor set himself up for the big booming slog sweep and missed. It did not look as plumb as the previous one, but umpire David upheld this after a good look. Afridi puts his hands up, he wanted that one. Taylor has a smile of resignation as he heads back. Replays say it was just clipping the top of off and middle.
Nathan gets a single down the ground to end the eventful over.
Nathan moves across and this goes straight over the top of leg stump.
short ball on off stump line, Nathan goes back and cuts square for one

The last time I saw a left-arm green shirt bowl those thunder yorkers was when Wasim Akram was still playing. Riaz has produced a missile here and Franklin's done well to protect his toes. No such luck for the furniture. 143 kph, from the moment Riaz released it, this was headed only one place - base of middle and off. Riaz knew it. Franklin knew it. He moved the feet to the leg side and played all over it, mostly in hope. Stumps are crashed. Riaz roars. Spectacular.
and a wide now on the off side as Oram lets it go
he's followed up a yorker from hell with two wides. This time well down the leg side and called.
overcooks the yorker on leg stump. 142 kph and Franklin works it through midwicket
and this one follows Natha McCullum's gloves like it has been programmed to do so. Short ball, swerves in dangerously and he does well to glove it to third man
Oram gets a single into the off side to end the over

Jake the snake, steals a boundary, by snaking the ball through a small gap in the off side. Slow off cutter at 117 kph, Oram gave himself room and then guided it with a dainty swish of the bat, between point and third man for four
Oram does it again. Fuller from Gul outside off, Oram gleefully opens up the off side and smears it in the air over backward point for another four.
this is a better length, very full outside off, almost a yorker and Oram can't do anything with it
hmm, did not have to do that, but Oram got away with it. He scurries across outside off, Gul follows him and the yorker goes between Oram and the stumps as he misses the shovel scoop.

Oram's gone, and the screws are tightening here. Unlucky in a sense, he picked long on with inch-perfect precision. Backs away to the leg side again, Gul tries to york him but it is just off the mark, so Oram gets under it and times the lofted swing pretty well. Just not good enough to clear the ropes
another yorker from Gul, at 146 kph and there's nothing Nathan can do with it. Digs it out to long on for a single. NZ need a lot more now.

somethings in Pakistan cricket never change. Like the fact that inevitably, Kamran Akmal will drop a catch. He's done it again. Short ball, Nathan gets a top edge behind his head and it was a dolly for Kamran who was moving back. And he put it down.
Mills turns the strike over with a tight single.

oh my, Nathan McCullum has hit this one out of New Zealand. Slower ball, he picked it early as he was moving around the crease, hanging well back in line with middle and off. It was in the slot, short and sitting up. He absolutely pulverised it over midwicket. Bang.
short ball, hurries into Nathan at good pace this time as he looks to pull, and gets a single
wide this time, Riaz needs to cut down on these here.
another tight single. Sirect hit may have got McCullum. Mills dabbed it away square and got across quickly for one

Nathan goes across the stumps and looks for the shovel scoop, but Riaz follows him with a very full yorker on off stump. Nathan can't do much with it, but gets a single though he doesn't connect, as it dribbles to the off side

tough catch, dropped at midwicket by Afridi. Nathan McCullum is waltzing all over the crease, backs away, goes across, jumps back into place and then looks to whack the short ball. He's tried to hit it so hard, he lost the grip on the bat as he tried to connect. Afridi ran to his right from midwicket and dived to his right but could not reach it. Great effort.

Nathan's perambulations at the crease come to an end. Again moves across to outside off stump before getting the front foot across to play the lap shot. Gul responds with a slow offcutter at 122 kph. Nathan did not make good contact with it, he seemed to play it onto the stumps.
full and fast, lands on leg stump and hits the pads as Bennett looks to flick. Appeal for lbw turned down.
short ball at 139 kph, onto Bennett a year before he tried to play it. Gets a single off the glove to backward point
bouncer at 138 kph, pushes Mills back in the crease and he keeps it away on the hop to the leg side. Furious stuff.
length ball at 145 kph on off stump, Bennett blocks to mid on and gets a single
back of a length outside off, Bennett keeps it out to the off side
wicked, inswinging yorker at 140 kph, Bennett did well to get the toes out of the way and dig it out to square leg for one
angles across him at 140 kph and beats him for pace as he shapes for the carve over the covers
on the stumps this time, short of a length again and worked off the pads towards mid on for a single
Pakistan have won the series in style. Take a bow! Riaz has finished it off with one back of a length outside off, Bennett hangs back and looks to steer it square. Inside edge thuds into the stumps.
